urlText: Services changes for Sydney Hobart Yacht Race
content:
Ferries will be affected on Boxing Day due to exclusion zones in effect around Circular Quay for the Sydney Hobart Yacht Race.
F1 Manly ferries will not run between Circular Quay and Manly between 11.45am and 3pm.
 
The last ferry leaves both Circular Quay and Manly at 11.45am with services resuming from Circular Quay at 2.50pm and from Manly at 3pm.
Buses replace Manly ferries during this time. Alternately catch buses from Manly Wharf to Manly Vale, Warringah Mall or Spit Junction to connect with frequent B-Line buses to and from the city during this time.
 
For more details on ferry service changes and other transport options, visit the visit the Sydney Hobart Yacht page.

urlText: Services changes for Sydney Hobart Yacht Race
content:
Ferries will be affected on Boxing Day due to exclusion zones in effect around Circular Quay for the Sydney Hobart Yacht Race.
 
F7 Double Bay ferries will not run between Circular Quay and Double Bay between 11am and 2pm/2.20pm.
 
The last ferry to Double Bay leaves Circular Quay at 10.57am with services resuming at 1.57pm. The last ferry to Circular Quay leaves Double Bay at 11.20am with services resuming at 2.20pm.
 
Catch route 324/325 buses to and from the city during this time.
 
For more details on ferry service changes and other transport options, visit the visit the Sydney Hobart Yacht page.
